{
  "stem": "15686.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But after that, either they extinguished the fire or it just burned itself out.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't know, but the walls were left standing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I saw it one time after I went back to Berlin after the war.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK, so what-- in the meantime, of course, my parents had seen the writing on the wall.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had made some preparations to leave Germany anyway.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we wanted to go to the United States, because we had some relatives here.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There's a little side story here.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My maternal grandmother had a young sister, who was a very beautiful girl, and during World War I, they lived in the Rhineland, which was occupied by the American Expeditionary Forces in 1918.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And a nice young Jewish man from The Bronx fell in love with my Great Aunt-- my grandmother's sister-- and she was a war bride.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he took her back to the United States to The Bronx.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And his name was George Helman.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that was my aunt-- great aunt Paula.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And through this great aunt being here in the United States-- in those days in the '30s, you needed someone to sponsor you to come to the United States.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And there was a quota of about 5,000 Jews from Germany a year.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And she had sent the necessary paper to us and to Washington.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But on the quota number, we were something like 22,000 something or other, which meant we had to wait about four years.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So now my father had to get out of Germany within 48 hours.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
